{"type":"answer","id":69694,"parentType":"question","parentId":10357,"uid":18025,"contents":"只有双十一一天的话，不行。一直算到新年，则可以的。<br>\n<br>\n作为参考，可以看一下美国感恩节到新年时期的销售状况：<br>\n<br>\n<a href=\"https://www.marketingcharts.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/NRF-Holiday-Retail-Sales-Growth-2002-2018-Feb2019.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.marketingcharts.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/NRF-Holiday-Retail-Sales-Growth-2002-2018-Feb2019.png\" alt=\"https://www.marketingcharts.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/NRF-Holiday-Retail-Sales-Growth-2002-2018-Feb2019.png\" style=\"max-width:100%\"></a><br>\n<br>\n对比同期美国的GDP增长<br>\n<br>\n<a href=\"https://www.economicshelp.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/us-economic-growth.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.economicshelp.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/us-economic-growth.png\" alt=\"https://www.economicshelp.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/us-economic-growth.png\" style=\"max-width:100%\"></a><br>\n<br>\n可以看到，两者的趋势是非常相似的。<br>\n<br>\n但是对比感恩节黑五周末与假期整体，会发现他们之间关系不大。<br>\n<br>\n<a href=\"http://www.zerohedge.com/sites/default/files/images/user3303/imageroot/2012/11-2/20121128_bf1.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://www.zerohedge.com/sites/default/files/images/user3303/imageroot/2012/11-2/20121128_bf1.png\" alt=\"http://www.zerohedge.com/sites/default/files/images/user3303/imageroot/2012/11-2/20121128_bf1.png\" style=\"max-width:100%\"></a><br>\n<br>\n在实践中，双十一近年增长稳定在35%左右，远远高出8%的经济增长速度，与黑五周末15%左右的增长高出1%的经济增长异曲同工。除非是如同2008那样的经济危机，否则应该比较难在双十一趋势中看到整体经济趋势。","date":"2019-11-01","agreeCount":10,"discussionCount":0}